<article class="blog-post">
  <div class="post-header">
    <span class="post-title">The Psychology of Money: Timeless Lessons on Wealth, Greed, and Happiness</span>
    <span class="post-date">Morgan Housel</span>
  </div>
  <div class="post-body">
    <p>Nineteen short stories about how people think about money. Financial success has less to do with what you know and more with how you behave. Patience, humility, and accepting that luck and risk are the same coin will take you further than any spreadsheet.</p>
    <p>Chapter 1 hits the hardest: no one is crazy with money, they just lived through different things. A person who grew up in poverty and a person who grew up wealthy will look at the same financial decision and reach opposite conclusions, both perfectly rational from where they stand. Your personal experience with money makes up maybe 0.00000001% of what has happened in the world, but it shapes 80% of how you think the world works.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="post-mood">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9734;</div>
  <div class="post-tags">
    <span class="tag">#finance</span>
    <span class="tag">#behavior</span>
    <span class="tag">#wealth</span>
  </div>
</article>

